#: model_terms:slide.slide,html_content:elearning_platform.slide_slide_51
msgid ""
"Good programmers don’t just write code that works — they write code that "
"others (and their future selves) can easily understand. Computers don’t care "
"if your code looks messy, but humans do. Clean, readable code is easier to "
"debug, maintain, and extend. In fact, professional programmers often spend "
"more time <em>reading</em> code than writing it. That’s why writing clear "
"code is as important as solving the problem itself."
msgstr ""
"优秀的程序员不仅编写能运行的代码——他们还编写能让其他人（以及未来的自己）轻松"
"理解的代码。计算机不在乎你的代码是否看起来混乱，但人类在乎。清晰、可读的代码"
"更易于调试、维护和扩展。事实上，专业程序员花在<em>阅读</em>代码上的时间往往比"
"编写代码更多。这就是为什么编写清晰的代码与解决问题本身同等重要。"

